aae0e93b-e579-4e25-86ee-0e22d36b48bc.290021e1-e107-4a31-a8de-beea89250218.prompt=Enter a value for xml aae0e93b-e579-4e25-86ee-0e22d36b48bc.371c98fe-928f-499a-b625-c9154d08bdf9.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.

This workflow adds the server components as children to server group in CSA. It adds relevant public actions and resource bindings to these server components.

Inputs\:


appComponentId - Application Service tier Component Id. 
providerId - CSA Resource Provider Id for the MOE provider
svcInstanceId - CSA Service Instance Id
ioXml - Output XML returned by the MOE Add Server or Create Service API calls
userIdentifier - CSA User Identifier
serviceName	- MOE Service Name created

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
aae0e93b-e579-4e25-86ee-0e22d36b48bc.e515bab1-b5a5-4138-914a-229d7e2d568c.description=
Takes a reference to XML (in the form of a String) and the specified XPath Query is run against the XML and returns the results in a form of a delimited list. The World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) organization provides the XPath specification (http\://www.w3.org).

Inputs\:
xml - The XML (in the form of a String)

xpathQuery - The XPath Query that is wanted to be run. See Examples in Notes section below.

delimiter- The delimiter used to separate values in the returnResult list. 

Default value\: ,

Result Value\:
returnResult - The result of the operation. If multiple XPaths are defined then this will add the delimiter between each value. There is no final delimiter.

Notes\:
Examples\:
The XPath Query can be specified as a single query in a format similiar to the following\:
/employees/employee[@id\="3"]/*[name()\="name" or name()\="jobDescription" or name()\="salary" or name()\="managerId"]/text()

This would return the following results\:
Goofy,tester,$50,1

Or if more then one XPath query needs to be specified, populate xpathQuery using the XPath concat function.  As an example here is sample of a xpathQuery value using XPath concat function\:
concat(/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/name/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/jobDescription/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/managerId/text(),',',/employees/employee[@id\="2"]/salary/text())

The output using the concat xpathQuery input would return the following results\:
Donald Duck,Lead Coder,1,$50

The examples above use the following xml string value\:


  
    Mickey Mouse
    Chief
    $100
    
  
  
    Donald Duck
    Lead Coder
    $50
    1
  
  
    Goofy
    tester
    $50
    1
  
  
    Pluto
    Coder - grade 1
    $25
    2
